description: This implementation of Tarjan's algorithm was originally based on GraphSCC by Iavor S. Diatchki: https://hackage.haskell.org/package/GraphSCC.

literal.string: Given a list of adjacency lists represented as (key, [key]) pairs, construct a graph along with a function mapping each vertex (an Int) back to its original key.
Compute the strongly connected components of the given graph. The components are returned in reverse topological order
Pop vertices off the stack until the given vertex is reached, collecting the current strongly connected component
Visit a vertex and recursively explore its successors
